-1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 162 "As you may have noted the addi
tion/subtraction operatios where carried out while the multiplication/
division operations were just indicated.  The Maple commands  " }
{TEXT 264 6 "expand" }{TEXT -1 6 " and  " }{TEXT 265 8 "simplify" }
{TEXT -1 298 "  can be used to rearrange and manipulate algebraic sums
 and products of polynomial expressions.  Go back to each of your calc
ulations of a., b., c. and d. and add to each line a command to expand
 the calculation and a command to simplify the caclulation.  E.g.,  th
e line for a. would change from:" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 1 " " }}
{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 4 "f*g;" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 3 "to " }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 32 "f*g; expa
nd(f*g); simplify(f*g);" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "
" 0 "" {TEXT -1 17 "Note the effect  " }{TEXT 268 6 "expand" }{TEXT 
-1 5 " and " }{TEXT 269 8 "simplify" }{TEXT -1 42 "  have on the way t
he calculation appears." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 
0 "" {TEXT -1 19 "The Maple commands " }{TEXT 266 16 "expand, simplify
" }{TEXT -1 5 " and " }{TEXT 267 6 "normal" }{TEXT -1 483 " can be use
 to rearrange, manipulate and simplify (cancel common factors) algebra
ic sums, products and quotients of rational expressions.   When a rati
onal expression is normalized, any common factors are cancelled.  Go b
ack to each of your calculations of e., f., g., h. and i. and add to e
ach line a command to expand the calculation, to normalize the calcula
tion, to simplify the calculation and both expand and normalize the ca
lculation.  E.g., the line for e. would change from:" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "
" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 6 "F*H/G;" }}}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 2 "to" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 
0 99 "F*H/G; expand(F*H/G); normal(F*H/G); simplify(F*H/G); expand(nor
mal(F*H/G)); normal(expand(F*H/G));" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" 
}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 17 "Note the effect  " }{TEXT 270 6 "expand
" }{TEXT -1 2 ", " }{TEXT 272 6 "normal" }{TEXT -1 3 ",  " }{TEXT 271 
8 "simplify" }{TEXT -1 10 " and both " }{TEXT 273 6 "expand" }{TEXT 
-1 5 " and " }{TEXT 274 6 "normal" }{TEXT -1 42 "  have on the way the
 calculation appears." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 
"" {TEXT -1 35 "2.  Factoring.  The Maple command  " }{TEXT 275 6 "fac
tor" }{TEXT -1 299 " can be used to factor algebraic polynomial expres
sions and rational expressions.  When rational expressions are factors
, any common factors are cancelled.  Factor each of the polynomials f,
 g, h, F, G and H.  Also, factor the algebraic and rational expression
s a., b., c., d., e., f., g., h. and i." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 
122 "a.  f*g                       b.   g*(h-f)                  c.   \+
f^3                 d.  (f + g)*(f - h) + (f - g)*(f + h)" }}{PARA 0 "
" 0 "" {TEXT -1 141 "e.  F*H/G                  f.   (F/H)/G          \+
       g.  F/(H/G)           h.    F/H*G                              \+
          i.   F/(H*G)" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG 
{PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 12 "factor(f*g);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" 
