0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 271 "3.  Fundamental The
orem of Algebra.  The Fundamental Theorem of Algebra asserts that ever
y non-constant polynomial (with complex-valued coefficients) has a roo
t (a zero, a solution).  A consequence of the Fundamental Theorem of A
lgebra is that every polynomial of degree " }{TEXT 276 1 "n" }{TEXT 
-1 13 " has exactly " }{TEXT 277 1 "n" }{TEXT -1 108 " roots.  An alte
rnate formulation of this consequence would be that every non-constant
 polynomial of degree " }{TEXT 279 1 "n" }{TEXT -1 38 " can be factore
d into a product of a  " }{TEXT 278 1 "n" }{TEXT -1 16 " linear factor
s." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 35 "Con
sider the following polynomials:" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 6 "I.    " }{XPPEDIT 19 1 "f := x^3-x^2-2*x" 
"6#>%\"fG,(*$%\"xG\"\"$\"\"\"*$F'\"\"#!\"\"*&F+F)F'F)F," }{TEXT -1 15 
"         II.   " }{XPPEDIT 19 1 "g := 6*x^3+11*x^2+6*x+1" "6#>%\"gG,*
*&\"\"'\"\"\"*$%\"xG\"\"$F(F(*&\"#6F(*$F*\"\"#F(F(*&F'F(F*F(F(F(F(" }
{TEXT -1 24 "                 III.   " }{XPPEDIT 19 1 "h := x^3-5*x+x^
2-5;" "6#>%\"hG,**$%\"xG\"\"$\"\"\"*&\"\"&F)F'F)!\"\"*$F'\"\"#F)F+F," 
}{TEXT -1 19 "                   " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 7 "IV.  \+
  " }{XPPEDIT 19 1 "F := x^4-144" "6#>%\"FG,&*$%\"xG\"\"%\"\"\"\"$W\"!
\"\"" }{TEXT -1 19 "             V.    " }{XPPEDIT 19 1 "G := 3*x^4+4*
x^3-2*x^2+x-6;" "6#>%\"GG,,*&\"\"$\"\"\"*$%\"xG\"\"%F(F(*&F+F(*$F*F'F(
F(*&\"\"#F(*$F*F/F(!\"\"F*F(\"\"'F1" }{TEXT -1 15 "         VI.   " }
{XPPEDIT 19 1 "H := x^5-x^2-2*x" "6#>%\"HG,(*$%\"xG\"\"&\"\"\"*$F'\"\"
#!\"\"*&F+F)F'F)F," }{TEXT -1 24 "                        " }}{PARA 0 
"" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 257 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 172 "Factor each po
lynomial and determine whether Maple was able to find enough linear fa
ctors to demonstrate the above assertion about the appropriate number \+
of linear factors." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "
> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 18 " f := x^3-x^2-2*x;" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" 
{XPPMATH 20 "6#>%\"fG,(*$)%\"xG\"\"$\"\"\"F**$)F(\"\"#F*!\"\"*&F-F*F(F
*F." }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 24 "g := 6*x^3+11*x^2+6*
x+1;" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#>%\"gG,**&\"\"'\"\"\")%\"xG\"
\"$F(F(*&\"#6F()F*\"\"#F(F(*&F'F(F*F(F(F(F(" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 
"" {MPLTEXT 1 0 19 "h := x^3-5*x+x^2-5;" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 
20 "6#>%\"hG,**$)%\"xG\"\"$\"\"\"F**&\"\"&F*F(F*!\"\"*$)F(\"\"#F*F*F,F
-" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 14 " F := x^4-144;" }}
{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#>%\"FG,&*$)%\"xG\"\"%\"\"\"F*\"$W\"!\"
\"" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 27 "G := 3*x^4+4*x^3-2*x^
2+x-6;" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#>%\"GG,,*&\"\"$\"\"\")%\"xG
\"\"%F(F(*&F+F()F*F'F(F(*&\"\"#F()F*F/F(!\"\"F*F(\"\"'F1" }}}{EXCHG 
{PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 17 "H := x^5-x^2-2*x;" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 
"" {XPPMATH 20 "6#>%\"HG,(*$)%\"xG\"\"&\"\"\"F**$)F(\"\"#F*!\"\"*&F-F*
F(F*F." }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 10 "factor(f);" }}
{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#*(%\"xG\"\"\",&F$F%F%F%F%,&F$F%\"\"#!
\"\"F%" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 10 "factor(g);" }}
{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#*(,&*&\"\"#\"\"\"%\"xGF'F'F'F'F',&*&\"
\"$F'F(F'F'F'F'F',&F(F'F'F'F'" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 
0 10 "factor(h);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#*&,&%\"xG\"\"\"F&F
&F&,&*$)F%\"\"#F&F&\"\"&!\"\"F&" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 
1 0 10 "factor(F);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#*&,&*$)%\"xG\"\"
#\"\"\"F)\"#7!\"\"F),&F%F)F*F)F)" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" 
