xG\"\"\"\"\"#F&F&,&F%F&F&!\"\"F&,(*&\"\"$F&)F%F'F&F&F%F&F,F&F&" }}}
{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 10 "factor(H);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 
"" {XPPMATH 20 "6#*(%\"xG\"\"\",&F$F%F%F%F%,**$)F$\"\"$F%F%*$)F$\"\"#F
%!\"\"F$F%F-F.F%" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 650 "In those cases where Maple did not find enough linear fa
ctors, there is a reason why Maple did not.  Maple makes an assumption
 that if the coefficients of a polynomial are all given exactly (as in
tegers or rational numbers [ratios of integer]), then you are only int
erested in finding exact factors (factors where the coefficients are i
ntegers or rational numbers).  The Fundamental Theorem of Algebra does
n't guarantee that the factors of  a polynomial will necessarily have \+
the same kind of coefficients as the polynomial, only the polynomial c
an be factored.  You can force Maple to report additional (approximate
) factors.  For example,  compare:" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}
{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 10 "factor(h);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 
"" {XPPMATH 20 "6#*&,&%\"xG\"\"\"F&F&F&,&*$)F%\"\"#F&F&\"\"&!\"\"F&" }
}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 18 "factor(h,sqrt(5));" }}
{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#*(,&%\"xG\"\"\"*$\"\"&#F&\"\"#!\"\"F&,
&F%F&F'F&F&,&F%F&F&F&F&" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "
" 0 "" {TEXT -1 25 "What is the difference?  " }{TEXT 308 0 "" }{TEXT 
309 88 "The difference is the second command factor found all the root
s in their exact values.  " }{TEXT -1 27 "The extra-term is called a \+
" }{TEXT 280 18 "field extension.  " }{TEXT -1 178 "Adding it tells Ma
ple to consider additonal factors where the coefficients are allowed t
o include elements from the field extension.  It is fairly clear from \+
the factoriztion of " }{TEXT 281 1 "h" }{TEXT -1 280 " all by itself t
hat something involving  sqrt(5)  would have to be included.  However,
 there are problems where there is not a obvious clue as to which spec
ific field extension should be added.  If you are willing to accept an
 appropriate solution, then using the field extension " }{TEXT 282 4 "
real" }{TEXT -1 179 " tells Maple to factor the polynomial using a flo
ating point approximation scheme.  For example, consider (here I am pr
etending I don't see that adding  sqrt(5) would be optimal):" }}{PARA 
0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 10 "fa
ctor(h);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#*&,&%\"xG\"\"\"F&F&F&,&*$)
F%\"\"#F&F&\"\"&!\"\"F&" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 15 "
factor(h,real);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#*(,&%\"xG\"\"\"$\"+
xz1OA!\"*F&F&,&F%F&$F&\"\"!F&F&,&F%F&$\"+xz1OAF)!\"\"F&" }}}{PARA 0 "
" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 91 "Finally, the Funda
mental Theorem of Algebra does not guarantee that a polynomial of degr
ee " }{TEXT 283 1 "n" }{TEXT -1 11 " will have " }{TEXT 284 1 "n" }
{TEXT -1 53 " real linear factors.  Rather, only hat it will have " }
{TEXT 285 1 "n" }{TEXT -1 134 " linear factors.  What is the differenc
e?  Some of the factors may involve complex roots rather than real roo
ts.  For example compare:" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG 
{PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 10 "factor(F);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" 
{XPPMATH 20 "6#*&,&*$)%\"xG\"\"#\"\"\"F)\"#7!\"\"F),&F%F)F*F)F)" }}}
{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 18 "factor(F,sqrt(3));" }}{PARA 
11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#*(,&*$)%\"xG\"\"#\"\"\"F)\"#7F)F),&F'F)*&F(F
)\"\"$#F)F(F)F),&F'F)*&F(F)F-F.!\"\"F)" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" 
{MPLTEXT 1 0 15 "factor(F,real);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#*(
,&%\"xG\"\"\"$\"+:;5kM!\"*F&F&,&F%F&$\"+:;5kMF)!\"\"F&,&*$)F%\"\"#F&F&
$\"+++++7!\")F&F&" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 18 "factor
(F,complex);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#**,&%\"xG\"\"\"$\"+:;5
kM!\"*F&F&,&F%F&^#F'F&F&,&F%F&^#$!+:;5kMF)F&F&,&F%F&$\"+:;5kMF)!\"\"F&
" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 126 "For
 the following polynomials demonstrate that each can be factored compl
etely into linear factors.  Use the field extensions " }{TEXT 286 4 "r
eal" }{TEXT -1 5 " and " }{TEXT 287 7 "complex" }{TEXT -1 36 " only if
 non-rational factors occur." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 
0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 7 " V.    " }{XPPEDIT 19 1 "G := 3*x^4+4*x^3-2*x^2+
x-6;" "6#>%\"GG,,*&\"\"$\"\"\"*$%\"xG\"\"%F(F(*&F+F(*$F*F'F(F(*&\"\"#F
(*$F*F/F(!\"\"F*F(\"\"'F1" }{TEXT -1 15 "         VI.   " }{XPPEDIT 
19 1 "H := x^5-x^2-2*x" "6#>%\"HG,(*$%\"xG\"\"&\"\"\"*$F'\"\"#!\"\"*&F
+F)F'F)F," }{TEXT -1 10 "          " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 7 "VII
.   " }{XPPEDIT 19 1 "f1 := 12*x^7+24*x^6-57*x^5-81*x^4+129*x^3+57*x^2
